{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":628,"text":"Salaam alaikum."},{"time":3544,"text":"Welcome to Doha."},{"time":5230,"text":"I am in charge of making this country's food secure."},{"time":8632,"text":"That is my job for the next two years,"},{"time":10683,"text":"to design an entire master plan,"},{"time":13099,"text":"and then for the next 10 years to implement it --"},{"time":16632,"text":"of course, with so many other people."},{"time":18652,"text":"But first, I need to talk to you about a story, which is my story,"},{"time":23299,"text":"about the story of this country that you're all here in today."},{"time":27167,"text":"And of course, most of you have had three meals today,"},{"time":30717,"text":"and probably will continue to have after this event."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35250,"text":"So going in, what was Qatar in the 1940s?"},{"time":39683,"text":"We were about 11,000 people living here."},{"time":43883,"text":"There was no water. There was no energy, no oil, no cars, none of that."},{"time":50899,"text":"Most of the people who lived here"},{"time":52294,"text":"either lived in coastal villages, fishing,"},{"time":54766,"text":"or were nomads who roamed around with the environment trying to find water."},{"time":60716,"text":"None of the glamour that you see today existed."},{"time":64118,"text":"No cities like you see today in Doha or Dubai or Abu Dhabi or Kuwait or Riyadh."},{"time":69266,"text":"It wasn't that they couldn't develop cities."},{"time":71883,"text":"Resources weren't there to develop them."},{"time":73982,"text":"And you can see that life expectancy was also short."},{"time":76815,"text":"Most people died around the age of 50."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78717,"text":"So let's move to chapter two: the oil era."},{"time":82516,"text":"1939, that's when they discovered oil."},{"time":85733,"text":"But unfortunately, it wasn't really fully exploited commercially"},{"time":90533,"text":"until after the Second World War."},{"time":92983,"text":"What did it do?"},{"time":95117,"text":"It changed the face of this country, as you can see today and witness."},{"time":98417,"text":"It also made all those people who roamed around the desert --"},{"time":102149,"text":"looking for water, looking for food,"},{"time":105433,"text":"trying to take care of their livestock -- urbanize."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109536,"text":"You might find this strange,"},{"time":111500,"text":"but in my family we have different accents."},{"time":115349,"text":"My mother has an accent that is so different to my father,"},{"time":119349,"text":"and we're all a population of about 300,000 people in the same country."},{"time":124383,"text":"There are about five or six accents in this country as I speak."},{"time":127917,"text":"Someone says, \"How so? How could this happen?\""},{"time":131733,"text":"Because we lived scattered."},{"time":133516,"text":"We couldn't live in a concentrated way simply because there was no resources."},{"time":138668,"text":"And when the resources came, be it oil,"},{"time":142479,"text":"we started building these fancy technologies"},{"time":145533,"text":"and bringing people together because we needed the concentration."},{"time":149183,"text":"People started to get to know each other."},{"time":151567,"text":"And we realized that there are some differences in accents."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155516,"text":"So that is the chapter two: the oil era."},{"time":158451,"text":"Let's look at today."},{"time":160566,"text":"This is probably the skyline that most of you know about Doha."},{"time":165292,"text":"So what's the population today?"},{"time":166683,"text":"It's 1.7 million people."},{"time":168933,"text":"That is in less than 60 years."},{"time":171632,"text":"The average growth of our economy is about 15 percent for the past five years."},{"time":177534,"text":"Lifespan has increased to 78."},{"time":180367,"text":"Water consumption has increased to 430 liters."},{"time":185176,"text":"And this is amongst the highest worldwide."},{"time":188583,"text":"From having no water whatsoever"},{"time":190750,"text":"to consuming water to the highest degree, higher than any other nation."},{"time":196234,"text":"I don't know if this was a reaction to lack of water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200000,"text":"But what is interesting about the story that I've just said?"},{"time":206200,"text":"The interesting part is that we continue to grow"},{"time":209383,"text":"15 percent every year for the past five years without water."},{"time":215983,"text":"Now that is historic. It's never happened before in history."},{"time":220933,"text":"Cities were totally wiped out because of the lack of water."},{"time":224866,"text":"This is history being made in this region."},{"time":227382,"text":"Not only cities that we're building,"},{"time":229299,"text":"but cities with dreams and people who are wishing to be scientists, doctors."},{"time":234452,"text":"Build a nice home, bring the architect, design my house."},{"time":237601,"text":"These people are adamant that this is a livable space when it wasn't."},{"time":243800,"text":"But of course, with the use of technology."},{"time":245769,"text":"So Brazil has 1,782 millimeters per year of precipitation of rain."},{"time":252283,"text":"Qatar has 74, and we have that growth rate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255134,"text":"The question is how."},{"time":257150,"text":"How could we survive that?"},{"time":260416,"text":"We have no water whatsoever."},{"time":262500,"text":"Simply because of this gigantic, mammoth machine called desalination."},{"time":268799,"text":"Energy is the key factor here. It changed everything."},{"time":272967,"text":"It is that thing that we pump out of the ground, we burn tons of,"},{"time":277466,"text":"probably most of you used it coming to Doha."},{"time":280466,"text":"So that is our lake, if you can see it."},{"time":283367,"text":"That is our river."},{"time":285216,"text":"That is how you all happen to use and enjoy water."},{"time":290558,"text":"This is the best technology that this region could ever have: desalination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297184,"text":"So what are the risks?"},{"time":299452,"text":"Do you worry much?"},{"time":301002,"text":"I would say, perhaps if you look at the global facts,"},{"time":304918,"text":"you will realize, of course I have to worry."},{"time":307509,"text":"There is growing demand, growing population."},{"time":310018,"text":"We've turned seven billion only a few months ago."},{"time":313267,"text":"And so that number also demands food."},{"time":316759,"text":"And there's predictions that we'll be nine billion by 2050."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319967,"text":"So a country that has no water"},{"time":322823,"text":"has to worry about what happens beyond its borders."},{"time":326474,"text":"There's also changing diets."},{"time":328806,"text":"By elevating to a higher socio-economic level,"},{"time":332872,"text":"they also change their diet."},{"time":335055,"text":"They start eating more meat and so on and so forth."},{"time":338055,"text":"On the other hand, there is declining yields"},{"time":340408,"text":"because of climate change and because of other factors."},{"time":343106,"text":"And so someone has to really realize when the crisis is going to happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348274,"text":"This is the situation in Qatar, for those who don't know."},{"time":352089,"text":"We only have two days of water reserve."},{"time":355439,"text":"We import 90 percent of our food,"},{"time":357723,"text":"and we only cultivate less than one percent of our land."},{"time":361423,"text":"The limited number of farmers that we have"},{"time":363872,"text":"have been pushed out of their farming practices"},{"time":367406,"text":"as a result of open market policy and bringing the big competitions, etc., etc."},{"time":372955,"text":"So we also face risks."},{"time":376206,"text":"These risks directly affect the sustainability of this nation and its continuity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383389,"text":"The question is, is there a solution?"},{"time":385907,"text":"Is there a sustainable solution?"},{"time":388089,"text":"Indeed there is."},{"time":390073,"text":"This slide sums up thousands of pages of technical documents"},{"time":394106,"text":"that we've been working on over the past two years."},{"time":396790,"text":"Let's start with the water."},{"time":398222,"text":"So we know very well -- I showed you earlier -- that we need this energy."},{"time":401991,"text":"So if we're going to need energy, what sort of energy?"},{"time":405089,"text":"A depletable energy? Fossil fuel?"},{"time":407388,"text":"Or should we use something else?"},{"time":409783,"text":"Do we have the comparative advantage to use another sort of energy?"},{"time":413122,"text":"I guess most of you by now realize that we do: 300 days of sun."},{"time":417256,"text":"And so we will use that renewable energy to produce the water that we need."},{"time":422588,"text":"And we will probably put 1,800 megawatts of solar systems"},{"time":427989,"text":"to produce 3.5 million cubic meters of water."},{"time":430598,"text":"And that is a lot of water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":432622,"text":"That water will go then to the farmers,"},{"time":434890,"text":"and the farmers will be able to water their plants,"},{"time":437127,"text":"and they will be able then to supply society with food."},{"time":441257,"text":"But in order to sustain the horizontal line --"},{"time":443374,"text":"because these are the projects, these are the systems that we will deliver --"},{"time":446705,"text":"we need to also develop the vertical line:"},{"time":449339,"text":"system sustenance, high-level education, research and development,"},{"time":454657,"text":"industries, technologies, to produce these technologies for application, and finally markets."},{"time":459719,"text":"But what gels all of it, what enables it, is legislation, policies, regulations."},{"time":465852,"text":"Without it we can't do anything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":468085,"text":"So that's what we are planning to do."},{"time":469637,"text":"Within two years we should hopefully be done with this plan"},{"time":473168,"text":"and taking it to implementation."},{"time":475135,"text":"Our objective is to be a millennium city, just like many millennium cities around:"},{"time":481835,"text":"Istanbul, Rome, London, Paris, Damascus, Cairo."},{"time":488970,"text":"We are only 60 years old, but we want to live forever"},{"time":493065,"text":"as a city, to live in peace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497626,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499571,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}